doc.after: Euclidean and non Euclidean geometries naturally have many similar properties namely those which do not depend upon the nature of parallelism This commonality is the subject of absolute geometry also called neutral geometry However the properties which distinguish one geometry from the others are the ones which have historically received the most attention
